SPUIG (Structured Prompts for UI Generation) generates indentation-based structured prompts that describe MUI component trees for AI consumption.

## Non-Obvious Conventions

- All MUI imports must be direct paths (`import Button from "@mui/material/Button"`), never barrel imports (`import { Button } from "@mui/material"`). Same for `@mui/icons-material`. Barrel imports add 200-800ms and thousands of unused modules.
- Context values always follow the `{ state, actions }` shape. State is read-only data, actions are callbacks. See `SpuigBuilderContext.ts` and `TreeNodeContext.ts` for the two context interfaces.
- This is React 19 ‚Äî use `use()` instead of `useContext()`, `ref` as a regular prop instead of `forwardRef`.
- State updates that depend on current state must use functional form: `setState(prev => ...)`.
- No test suite exists. There are no test commands, no test runner, no test files.

## Landmines

- The `isRoot` flag on `SpuigComponent` is special-cased throughout the entire codebase: Root components are excluded from SPUIG syntax output, skip validation, cannot be deleted or moved, and always render expanded. Any new feature touching components must account for `isRoot`.
- `CodeHighlighter` is lazy-loaded via `React.lazy()` in `SpuigPreview.tsx`. Do not convert it to a static import ‚Äî it pulls in the heavy `react-syntax-highlighter` bundle.
- All component tree mutations go through immutable utility functions in `spuigUtils.ts` (`addChildToComponent`, `removeComponentById`, `updateComponentById`, etc.). Never mutate component state directly.
- MUI component definitions live in JSON files under `src/data/components/`. The `muiComponents.ts` module aggregates them and provides indexed lookup via `getMuiComponentByName()`. Add new components by editing the JSON, not the aggregator.
- History (undo/redo) uses refs (`componentsRef`, `historyStateRef`) to avoid stale closures. `saveToHistory()` must be called before any `setComponents` mutation.

## Performance Rules (Progressive Disclosure)

Detailed performance patterns are in dedicated rules ‚Äî they apply automatically when relevant:

- `react-performance-critical.mdc` ‚Äî async waterfalls, Promise.all, bundle size, direct imports
- `react-rerender-optimization.mdc` ‚Äî derived state, memoization, useRef, transitions
- `react-rendering-performance.mdc` ‚Äî SVG animation, content-visibility, useTransition
- `react-javascript-performance.mdc` ‚Äî layout thrashing, index maps, caching, toSorted()
- `react-composition-patterns.mdc` ‚Äî compound components, context, boolean prop alternatives
- `react-advanced-patterns.mdc` ‚Äî init guards, handler refs, useEffectEvent
- `react-client-data-fetching.mdc` ‚Äî SWR, deduplicated listeners, localStorage
